# Patch: find-extract-search-api

Extracts only the API search function from upstream `src/find.ts`.

## Rationale

Hotskills' MCP server is non-interactive — it serves `tools/list` /
`tools/call` JSON-RPC over stdio, not a TTY prompt. Upstream `find.ts`
is the interactive `npx skills find` command: ANSI escape sequences,
raw-mode readline, fzf-style render loop, and a `runAdd(...)` shell-out
on selection. None of that is reachable from the MCP server.

The MCP server only needs `searchSkillsAPI(query)` — a pure HTTP call
returning `{ name, slug, source, installs }[]`.

## Removed symbols

- `runFind()` interactive entry point
- `runSearchPrompt()` and all readline / TTY handling
- ANSI escape constants (`RESET`, `BOLD`, `DIM`, `TEXT`, `CYAN`,
  `MAGENTA`, `YELLOW`, `HIDE_CURSOR`, `SHOW_CURSOR`, `CLEAR_DOWN`,
  `MOVE_UP`, `MOVE_TO_COL`)
- `formatInstalls()` helper (only used by the interactive renderer)
- `getOwnerRepoFromString()` helper
- `isRepoPublic()` helper
- All imports: `readline`, `runAdd`/`parseAddOptions`, `track`,
  `isRepoPrivate`
- All `track({event: 'find', ...})` telemetry calls

## Retained symbols

- `SEARCH_API_BASE` constant (unchanged)
- `SearchSkill` interface (verbatim)
- `searchSkillsAPI()` function (verbatim)

## Drift-check guidance

The drift-check workflow should diff only the `searchSkillsAPI`
function and its `SearchSkill` interface against the matching section
of upstream `src/find.ts`. The interactive UI surface is intentionally
not vendored and need not be tracked for drift.
